                                <p>Travelling with any airline and especially with a low-cost airline, but not sure about the baggage policy, means you may pay extra charges at the airport. Avoiding the surprised and cost at the airport in terms of baggage fees should be the priority of the passengers. Hence, check everything and terms of the airline baggage policy. Frontier is a major airline to fly, which is a low-cost airline as well, and is known for its cheapest airfare. If you are going to travel with this airline, then you must check the <b>Frontier checked bag size</b> and other baggage policy terms in this blog. Here is everything that you need to know –</p>
<H2>Checked Bag Size & Weight Limits</H2>
<p>Maximum dimensions: 62 linear inches (length + width + depth), including handles, wheels, and straps</p>
<p>Maximum weight: 40 lb (18.1 kg) or less</p>
<p>Bags exceeding either limit may incur fees or be refused</p>
<H3>What is the additional fee for an oversized bag on Frontier Airlines? </H3>
<H4>Additional Fees</H4>
<p>Overweight (41–50 lb): + $75 per bag, per direction</p>
<p>Overweight (51–100 lb): + $100 per bag, per direction</p>
<H4>Bags over 100 lb: Not accepted</H4>
<p>Oversize (63–110 linear inches): + $75 per bag, per direction</p>
<p>Bags over 110 inches: Not accepted</p>
<H2>Purchasing & Timing Tips</H2>
<p>Well, don’t think that checked bags are included with Basic Fare because with <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/frontier-airlines-flights-reservations.aspx"><b>Frontier airlines flights</b></a> only a small personal item is included in the price of the ticket for economy, premium or business fares. However, business fares may include checked bags and especially two checked bags. You can also buy the checked baggage and add-ons early, you will save significantly compared with paying at the airport or gate. </p>
<H3>Exceptions: Special Items & Military</H3>
<p>There are some items in the baggage policy for which airlines offer exceptions, and the essential devices are medical devices, baby gear, strollers, wheelchairs. These devices are allowed without counting toward your baggage allowance and are not subject to standard size/weight limits or fees. The Active U.S. military personnel may check up to two bags for free and are expect from overweight or oversize charges for their first two checked items. </p>
<H3>Real-World Notes & Enforcement</H3>
<p>The airline gate agents measure bags at the gate and may require fitting into their sizer and even for personal items or bag sizes that meet published limits. For the checked bag maximum dimension for the checked bag is ≤ 62 linear inches, and the maximum weight is 40 lb. A fee applies if your bag is overweight or oversized. In terms of the overweight baggage policy of Frontier Airlines, bags between 41–50 lb: +$75; 51–100 lb: +$100. Most important, 110 inches is not accepted. </p>
